       <table border="0" width="100%">             
 <tr>             
  <td width="100%">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;      
             
  <p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:方正隶书简体">日本学生如何发好汉语的“<span lang="EN-US">u”音<o:p>
</o:p>
</span></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:楷体_GB2312;
mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">李忠星</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:楷体_GB2312"><o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
text-indent:22.0pt"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">为了日本学生发好</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音，一些人想出了不少好办法。笔者曾悟出了一个简单、易行而又有效的方法，说出来供教学参考。</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt"><o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
text-indent:22.0pt"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">课堂上人手有一支笔。请学生将笔（最好是笔杆横截面为正六边形的）横放眼前的桌面上；低头用劲吹笔使之向前滚动。这时，为了将笔吹得滚动起来，学生势必自然地将上下唇合圆，向前伸得最远，唇肌紧张，以形成一个又圆又长的气流通道。这个通道正是发</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音所需要的声道。让学生保持将笔吹动时的口型，适当振动声带。这样，学生很快就能在一种简单有趣的游戏中体会并掌握发</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">的要领，轻轻松松地发出纯正的</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音来。</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt"><o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;
text-indent:22.0pt"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">不过，掌握了技巧不等于一定会在含有</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">及</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">的组合音的语流中发好</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音。事实上许多学汉语的日本学生在说话或朗读时，</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音仍然发不好而影响交际。原因在哪儿呢？日语中没有等同与</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">的音，而有一个相似又不同的う音。发う音，双唇不必合那么圆、伸那么远，唇肌不用那么紧张。当日本学生学习发</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音时，虽然较难，但经过启发还能发出纯正的汉语</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音。但在语流中，这种刚被唤醒的功能作用往往在“无意识”中被抵销了。</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">就被发成了う。因此，学汉语的日本学生要发好</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt">u</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:宋体;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">音，尤其要在语流中发好这个音以及日语中没有的其它一些如卷舌音，不仅要掌握好发音要领，更重要的是要认识到造成这些困难的原因本质上是来自心理上的，从而调节好言语心理机制，唤起并发挥言语传达系统先天就具有的或潜在的功能，使言语传达系统顺利地转换“角色”。而要完成这个过程，没有大量“下意识”的反复训练是不行的。这正象游泳能力的获取，更重要的是在“游泳”中学会游泳。</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt"><o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" align="right" style="text-align:right"><span style="font-family:
楷体_GB2312;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">（作者单位：武汉大学留学生教育学院）</span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-font-family:楷体_GB2312"><o:p>
</o:p>
</span></p>

                    
